(1)There shall be a Director of National Archives of Zambia who shall be a Director of National
public officer and who shall be responsible for the carrying out of the provisions of this Act. Archives of Zambia
(2) Without prejudice to the generality of subsection (1), the Director-
(a) shall direct, manage and control the National Archives;
(b) shall preserve, describe and arrange all public archives;
(c) shall accept and store any public records which are transferred to the
National Archives;
(d) may, if in his opinion it is necessary for their better preservation, bind or
repair any public archives;
(e) shall, at the request of a Government department, examine any public
records in the custody of such department and advise such department as
to the care and custody thereof;
